      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I'm putting together some personalized training programs for a new group of clients. I want to be as precise as possible with my programming. From a sports science perspective, are there any statistically significant biological differences in things like muscle fiber composition or bone density between different racial groups that I can use to help optimize their specific workouts?",
